---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy — Fractune">
  <nav class="nav">
    <div class="nav-inner">
      <a href="/" class="nav-logo"><img src="/logo.png" alt="" class="nav-logo-icon" />Fractune</a>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <main class="page">
    <div class="page-inner">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="last-updated">Version 1.0 — April 2026</p>

      <h2>1. Data Controller</h2>
      <p>
        Fractune is operated by Colours by Barslund (Anders Barslund), Abildgaardsvej 51,
        2830 Virum, Denmark. Phone: (+45) 60 63 40 24. For privacy inquiries, contact
        <a href="mailto:privacy@fractune.dk">privacy@fractune.dk</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Data We Collect</h2>
      <p>
        Fractune collects three categories of data:
      </p>

      <h3>a. Analysis Data</h3>
      <p>
        When you analyse a building, the app collects the following data points and
        submits them to the public dataset: D-value (fractal dimension), stability score,
        lacunarity, multi-scale profile, building selection mode, camera metadata (focal
        length, heading, pitch), and mask data. This data is anonymised and cannot be
        linked to you personally. All image processing takes place locally on your
        device — images are never uploaded to our servers.
      </p>

      <h3>b. Location Data (Optional)</h3>
      <p>
        GPS coordinates (latitude and longitude) and camera heading are collected only
        when you explicitly enable "Del position og retning" (Share position and
        direction) in the app. This data is attached to your analysis and published as
        part of the public dataset. You may disable location sharing at any time in the
        app settings.
      </p>

      <h3>c. Communications</h3>
      <p>
        If you contact us via email, we collect the information you provide, including
        your name and email address. This data is used solely to respond to your inquiry.
      </p>

      <h2>3. How We Use Data</h2>
      <p>We use the collected data for the following purposes:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>To improve the accuracy and reliability of the fractal analysis algorithms.</li>
        <li>To build and maintain the public fractal fluence map at <a href="https://sites.fractune.dk">sites.fractune.dk</a>.</li>
        <li>To support scientific research into the relationship between fractal geometry and architectural perception.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>4. Data Retention</h2>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Analysis data</strong> is retained indefinitely as part of the public dataset.</li>
        <li><strong>Support inquiries</strong> are retained for 3 months after resolution, then deleted.</li>
        <li><strong>Contributor ID</strong> — you may request deletion of your contributor ID and all associated contributions at any time. We will process your request within 30 days.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>5. Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>Fractune relies on the following third-party services:</p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Apple CloudKit</strong> — used to store and synchronise the public dataset. Subject to <a href="https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/" rel="noopener">Apple's privacy policy</a>.</li>
        <li><strong>Apple MapKit JS</strong> — used to display the map at sites.fractune.dk. Subject to <a href="https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/" rel="noopener">Apple's privacy policy</a>.</li>
      </ol>
      <p>
        We may share anonymised and aggregated analysis data with academic researchers
        for the purpose of scientific study.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Data Sharing</h2>
      <p>
        Anonymised analysis data is public by design. By contributing to the dataset,
        you acknowledge that your analysis results will be publicly accessible. We may
        share aggregated statistics with architecture researchers, urban planners, and
        academic institutions. We will never sell personal data to third parties.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Your Rights</h2>
      <p>
        Under applicable data protection law (including the GDPR), you have the right to:
      </p>
      <ol>
        <li>Access the data we hold about you.</li>
        <li>Request correction of inaccurate data.</li>
        <li>Request deletion of your data (including your contributor ID and all associated contributions).</li>
        <li>Request restriction of processing.</li>
        <li>Lodge a complaint with the Danish Data Protection Agency (Datatilsynet) at <a href="https://www.datatilsynet.dk" rel="noopener">datatilsynet.dk</a>.</li>
      </ol>
      <p>
        To exercise any of these rights, contact us at
        <a href="mailto:privacy@fractune.dk">privacy@fractune.dk</a> with your
        contributor ID (found under Settings in the app).
      </p>

      <h2>8. Children</h2>
      <p>
        Fractune is not directed at children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly
        collect personal data from children. If you believe a child has provided us with
        personal data, please contact us so we can take appropriate action.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this privacy policy from time to time. Significant changes will be
        announced in the app. The "Version" date at the top of this page indicates when
        this policy was last revised.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For all privacy-related questions, contact us at
        <a href="mailto:privacy@fractune.dk">privacy@fractune.dk</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .nav { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .nav-inner {
    max-width: var(--max-width);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 2rem;
    height: 52px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
  }
  .nav-logo { font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-text); display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.375rem; }
  .nav-logo-icon { height: 1.0em; width: auto; vertical-align: middle; transform: translateY(-1px); }
  .page { padding: 4rem 0; }
  .page-inner { max-width: 680px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 2rem; }
  h1 { font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .last-updated { color: var(--color-text-secondary); font-size: 0.875rem; margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }
  h2 { font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  h3 { font-size: 1.0625rem; font-weight: 600; margin-top: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  p { font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--color-text-secondary); margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  ol { font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--color-text-secondary); margin-bottom: 1rem; padding-left: 1.5rem; }
  li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
</style>
